{"word":"ἀέναος","slug":"ἀέναος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀέναος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἀένναος</el> is a corrupt form\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:νάω'><el>νάω</el></a> A\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>ever-flowing</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <i>everlasting</i>, <el>ἀρετᾶς ἀέναον κλέος</el> <b><a href='S:Simonides Lyricus'>Simon.</a></b>;—rare in attic Prose, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}